Had a bit of an epiphany

tags.name: family
tags.description: Can't live with them, can't live without them!

images.description:
Okay, I guess I don't really *HATE* hate my family (it is a rather strong word), it's just...idk how to explain. 
I would just honestly rather scrape out my eyeballs with a rusty garden trowel than have to do the Family Holiday Gatheringâ„¢ thing every single year. 

I'm 47 years old and finally moved away to another province (Canada) almost two years ago, and let me tell you, it was a breath of fresh air. And it is also wonderful to have a proper, demonstrable excuse to not attend the family "xmas festivities". But after giving it some thought, I had to admit to myself that I might actually find the holidays quite enjoyable if I could experience them with a person or people I actually WANTED to spend time with, people I love and who love & respect me for who I am.

And I may get the chance to start doing that soon, because this year I also finally found My Person, the one I've been searching for my entire life. He's the light in my world, and he feels the same way about me.
I am cautiously optimistic!
